The real rail. A signing helper produces `Access-Key` + `Access-Signature` (HMAC-SHA256 over `timestamp + method + path + body`) per SPEC §7.2; a TOTP helper (RFC 6238, SHA-1) derives crypto-withdrawal OTPs from `PDAX_TOTP_SECRET` for the refund path. Every call goes through `withRetry` (retry on network errors + 5xx, not on 4xx) and every response is parsed with Zod (untrusted). `traded_currency=XLM`, `settlement_currency=PHP`, fees on PHP. PHP cash-out sends **no** OTP. `import "server-only"`; never call from a browser.

